      "contents": "<div class=\"markitup-box\">\n\t\t\tFirstly, the status quo between Taiwan and China is that neither is subordinate to the other, and their respective areas of actual control don't affect each other. Secondly, while both Taiwan and China use the term \"China\" in their official full names currently, and their constitutions assert ownership of each other's territories, these are historical legacy issues that don't reflect the present reality and will eventually need correction. Thirdly, it's not the legal obligation of the  government of Taiwan or Taiwanese to take in refugees from China. The Taiwanese executive Yuan has also announced that mainland Chinese are no longer citizens of the Republic of China, and they don't enjoy the same rights as Taiwanese citizens.<br/>\nWhile this may disappoint some Anti-CCP and supporters of the Republic of China, it is an unavoidable situation given the current circumstances.\t\t</div>",
